## EJEMPLO 2: Barra Axial

Un resorte tiene rigidez **k**. Una barra axial tiene rigidez **k = EA/L**.
Misma matriz, solo cambia el valor de k.
@{end markdown}
%═══════════════════════════════════════

@{svg 600 180}
background #fafafa
% Apoyo
rect 30 55 12 80 fill:#888 stroke:#555 width:2
line 22 60 42 60 stroke:#555 width:1
line 22 80 42 80 stroke:#555 width:1
line 22 100 42 100 stroke:#555 width:1
line 22 120 42 120 stroke:#555 width:1
% Barra 1
rect 42 80 190 30 fill:#e3f2fd stroke:#1565c0 width:2
text 137 72 "EA/L₁" size:12 bold color:#1565c0 anchor:middle
circle 42 95 6 fill:#c62828 stroke:#b71c1c width:2
text 42 65 "1" size:14 bold color:#c62828 anchor:middle
circle 232 95 6 fill:#1565c0 stroke:#0d47a1 width:2
text 232 65 "2" size:14 bold color:#1565c0 anchor:middle
% Barra 2
rect 232 80 190 30 fill:#c8e6c9 stroke:#2e7d32 width:2
text 327 72 "EA/L₂" size:12 bold color:#2e7d32 anchor:middle
circle 422 95 6 fill:#1565c0 stroke:#0d47a1 width:2
text 422 65 "3" size:14 bold color:#1565c0 anchor:middle
% Fuerza
arrow 422 95 560 95 stroke:#e65100 width:3
text 565 95 "P" size:16 bold color:#e65100
% Datos
text 137 130 "L₁ = 2m" size:11 color:#1565c0 anchor:middle
text 327 130 "L₂ = 3m" size:11 color:#2e7d32 anchor:middle
text 300 158 "E=200 GPa, A=0.01 m², P=100 kN" size:11 bold color:#333 anchor:middle
@{end svg}

@{eqdef}
k = EA/L | Rigidez axial de una barra
k₁ = EA/L₁ | Barra 1 (nodos 1→2)
k₂ = EA/L₂ | Barra 2 (nodos 2→3)
@{end eqdef}

@{maxima}
E: 200e6;
A: 0.01;
L1: 2;
L2: 3;
P: 100;
k1: E*A/L1;
k2: E*A/L2;
/* Reducido (nodo 1 fijo) */
K_red: matrix([k1+k2, -k2],[-k2, k2]);
F_vec: matrix([0],[P]);
u: invert(K_red) . F_vec;
@{end maxima}

@{eqdef}
u₂ = P/k₁ = 0.0001 m = 0.1 mm | Desplazamiento nodo 2
u₃ = P(1/k₁ + 1/k₂) = 0.00025 m = 0.25 mm | Desplazamiento nodo 3
@{end eqdef}

%═══════════════════════════════════════
@{markdown}
---
## EJEMPLO 3: Viga en Flexion

El salto: de **1 DOF** a **2 DOF** por nodo.
En vigas cada nodo tiene desplazamiento **v** y rotacion **θ**.
La matriz local pasa de 2×2 a **4×4**.
@{end markdown}

@{svg 600 190}
background #fafafa
% Viga
rect 60 75 480 18 fill:#e8eaf6 stroke:#3f51b5 width:2
% Empotrado izquierdo
rect 40 58 20 55 fill:#888 stroke:#555 width:2
line 32 63 60 63 stroke:#555 width:1
line 32 78 60 78 stroke:#555 width:1
line 32 93 60 93 stroke:#555 width:1
line 32 108 60 108 stroke:#555 width:1
% Roller derecho
circle 540 103 7 fill:none stroke:#888 width:2
line 527 110 553 110 stroke:#888 width:2
% Nodos
circle 60 84 5 fill:#c62828 stroke:#b71c1c width:2
text 60 55 "1" size:14 bold color:#c62828 anchor:middle
circle 300 84 5 fill:#1565c0 stroke:#0d47a1 width:2
text 300 55 "2" size:14 bold color:#1565c0 anchor:middle
circle 540 84 5 fill:#1565c0 stroke:#0d47a1 width:2
text 540 55 "3" size:14 bold color:#1565c0 anchor:middle
% Carga
arrow 300 30 300 73 stroke:#e65100 width:3
text 300 22 "P = 10 kN" size:12 bold color:#e65100 anchor:middle
% DOFs
text 60 128 "v₁, θ₁" size:10 color:#c62828 anchor:middle
text 300 128 "v₂, θ₂" size:10 color:#1565c0 anchor:middle
text 540 128 "v₃, θ₃" size:10 color:#1565c0 anchor:middle
text 180 103 "L = 3m" size:11 color:#3f51b5 anchor:middle
text 420 103 "L = 3m" size:11 color:#3f51b5 anchor:middle
text 300 155 "2 DOF/nodo × 3 nodos = 6 DOF total" size:11 bold color:#333 anchor:middle
text 300 172 "EI = 20000 kN·m²" size:11 color:#555 anchor:middle
@{end svg}

@{eq}
[k]_viga = (EI/L³) × | 12    6L   -12   6L  |
                       | 6L    4L²  -6L   2L² |
                       | -12  -6L    12  -6L  |
                       | 6L    2L²  -6L   4L² |
@{end eq}

@{maxima}
EI: 20000;
L: 3;
/* Matriz local viga Euler-Bernoulli 4x4 */
k_viga: (EI/L^3) * matrix(
  [12,    6*L,   -12,   6*L  ],
  [6*L,   4*L^2, -6*L,  2*L^2],
  [-12,  -6*L,    12,  -6*L  ],
  [6*L,   2*L^2, -6*L,  4*L^2]
);
@{end maxima}

@{maxima}
EI: 20000;
L: 3;
c: EI/L^3;
/* Ensamblar 6x6, luego reducir */
/* BC: v1=0, th1=0 (empotrado), v3=0 (roller) */
/* Libres: v2 (DOF 3), th2 (DOF 4), th3 (DOF 6) */
K_red: matrix(
  [24*c,    0,        6*L*c  ],
  [0,       8*L^2*c,  2*L^2*c],
  [6*L*c,   2*L^2*c,  4*L^2*c]
);
F_red: matrix([10],[0],[0]);
u_red: float(invert(K_red) . F_red);
@{end maxima}

%═══════════════════════════════════════
@{markdown}
